UNTYPED_ATOMIC

public static final Type UNTYPED_ATOMIC
Additional XMD type 'untyped value'. It denotes untyped atomic data, such as text that has not been assigned a more specific type. An attribute that has been validated in skip mode is represented in the Data Model by an attribute node with the type xs:untypedAtomic.

UNTYPED

public static final Type UNTYPED
Additional XMD type 'untyped'. It denotes the dynamic type of an element node that has not been validated, or has been validated in skip mode.

XML Schema type 'string'. The string datatype represents character strings in XML.

DATE_TIME

public static final Type DATE_TIME
XML Schema type 'dateTime'. dateTime values may be viewed as objects with integer-valued year, month, day, hour and minute properties, a decimal-valued second property, and a boolean timezoned property.

TIME

public static final Type TIME
XML Schema type 'time'. time represents an instant of time that recurs every day.

DATE

public static final Type DATE
XML Schema type 'date'. The "value space" of date consists of top-open intervals of exactly one day in length on the timelines of dateTime, beginning on the beginning moment of each day (in each timezone), i.e. '00:00:00', up to but not including '24:00:00' (which is identical with '00:00:00' of the next day).

G_YEAR_MONTH

public static final Type G_YEAR_MONTH
XML Schema type 'gYearMonth'. gYearMonth represents a specific gregorian month in a specific gregorian year.

G_YEAR

public static final Type G_YEAR
XML Schema type 'gYear'. gYear represents a gregorian calendar year.

G_MONTH_DAY

public static final Type G_MONTH_DAY
XML Schema type 'gMonthDay'. gMonthDay is a gregorian date that recurs, specifically a day of the year such as the third of May.

G_DAY

public static final Type G_DAY
XML Schema type 'gDay'. gDay is a gregorian day that recurs, specifically a day of the month such as the 5th of the month.

G_MONTH

public static final Type G_MONTH
XML Schema type 'gMonth'. gMonth is a Gregorian month that recurs every year.

BOOLEAN

public static final Type BOOLEAN
XML Schema type 'boolean'. boolean has the "value space" required to support the mathematical concept of binary-valued logic: {true, false}.

DECIMAL

public static final Type DECIMAL
XML Schema type 'decimal'. decimal represents a subset of the real numbers, which can be represented by decimal numerals.

INTEGER

public static final Type INTEGER
XML Schema type 'integer'. integer is derived from decimal by fixing the value of fractionDigits to be 0 and disallowing the trailing decimal point. This results in the standard mathematical concept of the integer numbers. The value space of integer is the infinite set {...,-2,-1,0,1,2,...}.

LONG

public static final Type LONG
XML Schema type 'long'. long is "derived" from integer by setting the value of "maxInclusive" to be 9223372036854775807 and "minInclusive" to be -9223372036854775808.

INT

public static final Type INT
XML Schema type 'int'. int is "derived" from long by setting the value of "maxInclusive" to be 2147483647 and "minInclusive" to be -2147483648.

SHORT

public static final Type SHORT
XML Schema type 'short'. short is "derived" from int by setting the value of "maxInclusive" to be 32767 and "minInclusive" to be -32768.

BYTE

public static final Type BYTE
XML Schema type 'byte'. byte is "derived" from short by setting the value of "maxInclusive" to be 127 and "minInclusive" to be -128.

NON_POSITIVE_INTEGER

public static final Type NON_POSITIVE_INTEGER
XML Schema type 'nonPositiveInteger'. nonPositiveInteger is "derived" from integer by setting the value of "maxInclusive" to be 0. This results in the standard mathematical concept of the non-positive integers. The "value space" of nonPositiveInteger is the infinite set {...,-2,-1,0}.

NEGATIVE_INTEGER

public static final Type NEGATIVE_INTEGER
XML Schema type 'negativeInteger'. negativeInteger is "derived" from nonPositiveInteger by setting the value of "maxInclusive" to be -1. This results in the standard mathematical concept of the negative integers. The "value space" of negativeInteger is the infinite set {...,-2,-1}.

NON_NEGATIVE_INTERGER

public static final Type NON_NEGATIVE_INTERGER
XML Schema type 'nonNegativeInteger'. nonNegativeInteger is "derived" from integer by setting the value of "minInclusive" to be 0. This results in the standard mathematical concept of the non-negative integers. The "value space" of nonNegativeInteger is the infinite set {0,1,2,...}.

POSITIVE_INTEGER

public static final Type POSITIVE_INTEGER
XML Schema type 'positiveInteger'. positiveInteger is "derived" from nonNegativeInteger by setting the value of "minInclusive" to be 1. This results in the standard mathematical concept of the positive integer numbers. The "value space" of positiveInteger is the infinite set {1,2,...}.

UNSIGNED_LONG

UNSIGNED_SHORT

UNSIGNED_BYTE

NORMALIZED_STRING

public static final Type NORMALIZED_STRING
XML Schema type 'normalizedString'. normalizedString represents white space normalized strings. The "value space" of normalizedString is the set of strings that do not contain the carriage return (#xD), line feed (#xA) nor tab (#x9) characters. The "lexical space" of normalizedString is the set of strings that do not contain the carriage return (#xD), line feed (#xA) nor tab (#x9) characters.

TOKEN

public static final Type TOKEN
XML Schema type 'token'. token represents tokenized strings. The "value space" of token is the set of strings that do not contain the carriage return (#xD), line feed (#xA) nor tab (#x9) characters, that have no leading or trailing spaces (#x20) and that have no internal sequences of two or more spaces. The "lexical space" of token is the set of strings that do not contain the carriage return (#xD), line feed (#xA) nor tab (#x9) characters, that have no leading or trailing spaces (#x20) and that have no internal sequences of two or more spaces.

LANGUAGE

public static final Type LANGUAGE
XML Schema type 'language'. language represents natural language identifiers as defined by [RFC 3066]. The "value space" of language is the set of all strings that are valid language identifiers as defined [RFC 3066] . The "lexical space" of language is the set of all strings that conform to the pattern [a-zA-Z]{1,8}(-[a-zA-Z0-9]{1,8})* .

NAME

public static final Type NAME
XML Schema type 'name'. Name represents XML Names. The "value space" of Name is the set of all strings which "match" the Name production of [XML 1.0 (Second Edition)]. The "lexical space" of Name is the set of all strings which "match" the Name production of [XML 1.0 (Second Edition)].

NCNAME

public static final Type NCNAME
XML Schema type 'NCName'. NCName represents XML "non-colonized" Names. The "value space" of NCName is the set of all strings which "match" the NCName production of Namespaces in XML. The "lexical space" of NCName is the set of all strings which match the NCName production of [Namespaces in XML].

ID

public static final Type ID
XML Schema type 'ID'. ID represents the ID attribute type from [XML 1.0 (Second Edition)]. The "value space" of ID is the set of all strings that "match" the NCName production in [Namespaces in XML]. The "lexical space" of ID is the set of all strings that "match" the NCName production in [Namespaces in XML].

The "lexical space" of IDREF is the set of strings that "match" the NCName production in Namespaces in XML.

ENTITY

public static final Type ENTITY
XML Schema type 'ENTITY'. ENTITY represents the ENTITY attribute type from XML 1.0 (Second Edition). The "value space" of ENTITY is the set of all strings that "match" the NCName production in [Namespaces in XML] and have been declared as an unparsed entity in a document type definition. The "lexical space" of ENTITY is the set of all strings that "match" the NCName production in [Namespaces in XML].
